## Why this is separate from the code license

The paper text and the source code are **separate works** with **separate
licenses**. The Kontablo *source code* is licensed under the Business Source
License 1.1 (see the repository-root `LICENSE` and `LICENSING.md`); the *paper
text* is CC BY 4.0 as stated above. This matches the license selected for the
same preprint on Zenodo, SSRN, ResearchGate, and (when posted) arXiv, so the
paper carries one consistent license across every distribution channel.
